 Introduction to Web Development, Setup, and HTML Basics
What I Learned:

How websites work: client, server, HTTP/HTTPS

Basic structure of HTML: <html>, <head>, <body>

Common tags: <h1>, <p>, <a>, <img>, <ul>, <li>

Setting up VS Code with Live Server extension

Practice Exercise: Create a personal introduction page

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>My First Webpage</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Welcome to My Learning Journey</h1>
    <p>Hello! I'm starting my Full Stack Web Development journey today.</p>
    <h2>My Goals:</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Learn HTML, CSS, JavaScript</li>
        <li>Build responsive websites</li>
        <li>Master backend development</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Connect with me: <a href="#">Coming Soon</a></p>
</body>
</html>

